              "id": "CVE-2023-6378",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "logback: serialization vulnerability in logback receiver"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A serialization vulnerability in logback receiver component part of \nlogback version 1.4.11 allows an attacker to mount a Denial-Of-Service \nattack by sending poisoned data.\n\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-6378",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2023-6378\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: ch.qos.logback:logback-core\nFixed Version: 1.3.12, 1.4.12, 1.2.13\nLink: [CVE-2023-6378](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-6378)\nA serialization vulnerability in logback receiver component part of \nlogback version 1.4.11 allows an attacker to mount a Denial-Of-Service \nattack by sending poisoned data.\n\n",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2023-6378**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|ch.qos.logback:logback-core|1.3.12, 1.4.12, 1.2.13|[CVE-2023-6378](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-6378)|\n\nA serialization vulnerability in logback receiver component part of \nlogback version 1.4.11 allows an attacker to mount a Denial-Of-Service \nattack by sending poisoned data.\n\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 7.1,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:N/I:N/A:H",
