            {
              "id": "CVE-2022-40151",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "xstream: Xstream to serialise XML data was vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Those using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2022-40151\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream\nFixed Version: 1.4.20\nLink: [CVE-2022-40151](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151)\nThose using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2022-40151**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream|1.4.20|[CVE-2022-40151](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151)|\n\nThose using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack."
              },
              "properties": {
