            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-33870",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "io.netty/netty-codec-http: Netty: Request smuggling via incorrect parsing of HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Netty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33870",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-33870\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: io.netty:netty-codec-http\nFixed Version: 4.1.132.Final, 4.2.10.Final\nLink: [CVE-2026-33870](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33870)\nNetty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-33870**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|io.netty:netty-codec-http|4.1.132.Final, 4.2.10.Final|[CVE-2026-33870](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33870)|\n\nNetty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue."
